# Alfred Pack — Cursor rules (repo root)

Native Cursor tools (Read, Grep, Glob, Shell, Edit, Write) are the **default** for repo work.

## Tool layers (one primary path per task)
1. **Native tools** — code, config, git, tests in this repo
2. **Domain MCPs** — Excel, Power BI, GitHub, browser, etc. (see `skills/mcp-routing.md`)
3. **lean-ctx** — optional for large file maps, compressed shell, session memory (`skills/lean-ctx.md`)

If any MCP errors or exceeds ~5 seconds, stop using it for the rest of the turn and use native tools.

## Coding
Follow `AGENTS.md` and `skills/karpathy-coding-guidelines.md`. Smallest change that solves the task.

## Structure
Rules, skills, MCP usage, and learning workflow: **`docs/ALFRED-STRUCTURE.md`**
